ElementDescription: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject
Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project
Date on which the interview/genetic test/sampling/imaging/biospecimen was completed. MM/DD/YYYY
Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging.
Notes: Age is rounded to chronological month. If the research participant is 15-days-old at time of interview, the appropriate value would be 0 months. If the participant is 16-days-old, the value would be 1 month.

ElementDescription: Sex of subject at birth
Notes: M = Male; F = Female; O=Other; NR = Not reported

ElementDescription: Avatar selected by the participant
Notes: 0=Spiderman; 1=Black Panther; 2=Pikachu; 3=Chloe (the cat from secret life of pets)

ElementDescription: Probability on a given trial that alien 1 (left planet, left alien) will yield a reward if chosen
Probability on a given trial that alien 2 (left planet, right alien) will yield a reward if chosen
Probability on a given trial that alien 3 (right planet, left alien) will yield a reward if chosen
Probability on a given trial that alien 4 (right planet, right alien) will yield a reward if chosen
Trial number
Reaction time for stage 1 choice (milliseconds)
Stage 1 choice
Whether transition is common (70% of trials) or rare (30% of trials)
Stage 2 state reached
Reaction time for stage 2 choice (milliseconds)
Stage 2 choice
Whether a reward was received on the current trial
Duration of trial from start to end (milliseconds)
Notes: Includes time taken (in milliseconds) by task animations, not just reaction times.

ElementDescription: Color of the portal (stage 1 choice) on the left
Color of the portal (stage 1 choice) on the right
Percentage of Stage 1 choice that is 0
Notes: 0 = 100% choice is 1 (0% choice is 0); 100 = 100% choice is 0 (100% choice is 1); -999 = NA or Missing

ElementDescription: Percentage of transition that is common
Notes: 0 = 0% transition is common; 100 = 100% transition is common; -999 = NA or Missing

ElementDescription: Percentage of reward received on the current trial
Notes: 0 = 0% chance of reward; 100 = 100% chance of reward; -999 = NA or Missing
